com.milk.uberchat.iface
Interface ChatIdentity

All Superinterfaces:
ChatChannelHolder, ChatEntity, ChatLocus, Commandable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseIdentity
public interface ChatIdentity
extends ChatChannelHolder

This interface encapsulates a user identity, generally a particular userid on a particular chat system. This kept as a separate interface from ChatSystem itself to allow for the possibility of multiple active identities on the same system. As a ChatLocus, a ChatIdentity is about sending and/or receiving system-wide messages for the given identity.

Author:
Dan Bornstein, danfuzz@milk.com
